				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I did not see
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">/pet as you were</span>
<br />

<br />
As I understand, this clears all previous pet commands. Very useful when you targetted a MOB, asked Jobober to attack, and the MOB was out of range. If you do not do this, you may end up with an unexpected encounter when the MOB wanders back into range later. Pets apparently have a target list that you add to when you /pet attack; you can stack at least 5-10 targets on that list, from what I have tried, and they will be attacked by your pet.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
