				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've never seen /pet attack add the target I have specified to the <span style="font-style: italic">top</span> of the pets hate list.  It just adds it to the list at the lowest hate level.  The pet will not (if in combat with a mob currently) stop attacking its current target and switch to the new one just with this command, you need to specifically tell it to back off first, and then attack the new target.
<br />

<br />
(This is pretty easy to demonstrate in a group situation where the pet is not tanking and therefore is not constantly having more hate from its current target overriding your new attack command).<br />_________________<br />63rd Arch Mage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=341656" target="_blank" class="postlink">Yarril</a> of the <a href="http://www.grey-council.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">Grey Council</a> on Xev</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
