			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What about <span style="font-weight: bold">/pet guard me</span>? How is it significantly different than <span style="font-weight: bold">/pet follow me</span>?
<br />

<br />
On raids it's wise to <span style="font-weight: bold">/pet taunt off</span>. If for whatever reason the most hated PC is out of melee range, a pet taunting <span style="font-style: italic">can</span> put the pet at the top of the mob's hate list.
<br />

<br />
This goes further into detail how Taunt is "supposed" to work. A successful taunt by a PC or pet will put that PC or pet at the top of the hate list. If a PC is out of melee range when the pet taunts, the pet will be put at the top of the hate list and thus gain undesired aggro.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://members.cox.net/jmattcrews/xalsig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row2" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
