				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/pet guard me and /pet follow me are now the same thing
<br />

<br />
However, long, long, long ago. . .  the /pet guard me used to put the pet into attack mode of any NPC that wandered by.  They changed it after awhile, I guess to many complaints.
<br />

<br />
If you did /pet guard me, the pet would follow you around and attack anything near you.  Great for wiping out newbie area, until you run up near a guard of course.
<br />

<br />
We were camping Icy orcs.  The other mage had pet in /guard mode.  Sitting down medding.  Tundra Jack walks up behind us and her pet attacks.  Smooshed magician.<br />_________________<br /><DIV *****"position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FF0000)"><a *****"font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796  target="new-window"><b>Master Zacatac Soulwanderer</b></a></div>"1450 Club" Member</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
